reviews.title: Definitely highly recommended!
reviews.text:
Brasserie George in Amsterdam was a wonderful surprise. I had checked it out some time ago and saw mostly mediocre reviews, so I wasn’t expecting much. 

But it was very pleasantly surprising – the ambiance was great, the dishes were delicious (brasserie style), and the service was quick! We had the special menu for Sail 2025, which was very tasty, along with a few other dishes from the regular menu. Definitely highly recommended!

reviews.title: Delicious Chicken and Warm Hospitality!
reviews.text:
Delicious Chicken and Warm Hospitality!

We had a wonderful experience today. The chicken was excellent in quality, and Bram welcomed us very warmly. Although it was quite crowded, we still enjoyed it a lot. If we come to Amsterdam again, we will definitely return to this restaurant. We had heard about it from friends, and visiting today turned out to be a truly wonderful experience.
Rohini ♥️

reviews.title: thumbs up for George
reviews.text:
We loved Brasserie George and George Deli. Professional friendly staff. Organised and attentive. Atmosphere was so nice. It was a pretty busy evening but we did not wait long for water, bread/ olives and food service. Drinks were generous and the food was excellent. And the prices are so reasonable. We would definitely come back.
My daughter works there but that is not why we would come back. She is very happy with her managers and how they treat their employees. Happy staff= great service, food and vibe.

mgmtResponse.text:
Dear Olga, thank you so much for sharing such a thoughtful and kind review! We’re thrilled to hear you had such a great experience at both Brasserie George and George Deli. It’s wonderful that the staff’s professionalism and attentiveness stood out to you, and we’re delighted to know you enjoyed the atmosphere, food, and drinks as well.

We’re especially proud that your daughter is happy with her team and the work environment — it’s clear that a positive staff dynamic translates into excellent service, and it means a lot to us that you noticed. We can’t wait to welcome you back soon!

See you next time!

reviews.title: Disappointing experience at Brasserie George
reviews.text:
This afternoon I went to Brasserie George, a place around the corner from me. Unfortunately, it was quite a disappointment.

We were welcomed by an inexperienced young waitress, which immediately made for a messy start. After some back-and-forth, our coats were adopted. The temperature in the store was moderate, but fortunately there was a shabby gas stove at our table.

When handing over the drinks menu, I immediately asked for the menu, so we could match our drinks to the food. This all went rather awkwardly and was accompanied by the remark ‘quite right’ three times. What's absolutely right if I don't have anything yet? This kind of turbo-speak simply has no place in a restaurant.

The food itself was acceptable, but the prices really made no sense. Some examples:

A bottle of water: €7,00
A few pieces of bread with olives: €12,00
A steak tartare the size of a mustard pot lid, without any garnish: €14,00
A grilled house steak, without anything: €24,00
The portions were meagre, and as a finishing touch the cheese plate (€14.00) came with three poor pieces of cheese, straight from the fridge and stone cold. When I reported this, there was a silly reaction by yet another waitress without any knowledge of the facts.

That was the point for me to settle and leave the business. Brasserie George, I wish you all the best of luck, but for me it's just this one experience.

mgmtResponse.text:
Het spijt ons te horen dat uw ervaring bij Brasserie George teleurstellend was. Het is absoluut niet de indruk die we willen achterlaten bij onze gasten, en we nemen uw feedback zeer serieus.

We begrijpen dat de ontvangst en de service niet naar verwachting waren, en we zullen dit zeker bespreken met ons team om ervoor te zorgen dat dit in de toekomst beter verloopt. Wat betreft de gerechten en prijzen, we zijn dankbaar dat u ons hierop wijst. We willen altijd dat onze gasten de best mogelijke waarde krijgen voor hun ervaring, en we zullen uw opmerkingen over de porties en prijs-kwaliteitverhouding zeker herzien.

De reactie op het kaasplankje is inderdaad niet hoe we willen dat onze gasten zich voelen. We bieden onze excuses aan voor het ongemak en zullen ervoor zorgen dat dit niet nogmaals voorkomt.

We hopen dat u ons in de toekomst nog een kans wilt geven om een betere ervaring te bieden. Dank u voor uw eerlijke feedback, en we wensen u het beste.

Team Brasserie George

tips.body: Er moet hier eens goed geëvalueerd worden. E.e.a. ligt niet in verhouding met de prijzen.

reviews.title: Food was a let down
reviews.text: It’s very new - the set up is nice the service is good but they seem a bit disorganised. The food was average: bread and butter very nice, sardines good although too much bread crumbs on these; I had the razor clams in wine and it was so oily - couldn’t even taste the white wine; the bbq autumn greens were also very oily; my husband had the gnocchi - okayish. Food very oily the kitchen should re look  at the amount of oil they use. I think we may go back just for drinks.

mgmtResponse.text:
Thank you for your feedback! We're glad to hear that you liked the setup and service, though we're sorry to hear that the food didn’t meet your expectations. We truly appreciate your honesty and will definitely pass your comments about the oil usage along to the kitchen team for review. It's important to us that each dish is balanced and flavorful, and we’ll make sure to address this with our chefs.

We’re also happy you’re considering returning for drinks, and we’d love the chance to provide you with a better dining experience next time. Your feedback is invaluable, and we hope to see you again soon!

Three days doesn’t sound like much, but in Amsterdam—a small, walkable city with attractions clustered in its city center—it’s plenty of time. In three days you can check off all the must-dos, from masterpieces by Vermeer and van Gogh to beer in a brown cafe to snapping a charming canal photo (or ten).  The itinerary below packs together Amsterdam’s hit list with downtime for wandering over canal bridges, dining, and drinking.

Amsterdam is said to have two sides. There’s the charming side: quaint cobblestone streets that lead to picture-perfect canals lined with adorable gabled houses. And there’s the rowdy side: the lively Red Light District where you’ll find strip clubs and “coffee shops” selling cannabis. But there’s so much more to the city—like its many colorful outdoor markets, the street art in the once-abandoned shipyards of Amsterdam-Noord, and the bright tulip fields just beyond the capital. And with seven days, you’ll have the time to explore it all.

articleContent.title: The best time to visit Amsterdam

seoInfo.metaDescription: When to visit for tulips, ideal weather, fewer crowds, and great deals

As a repeat visitor, I’ve never run out of reasons to return to Amsterdam. That’s because this city easily holds its own against other European capitals, thanks to its amazing architecture (especially those 17th-century canal houses), top-tier museums (all those Van Gogh sunflowers), and a dining scene that constantly punches above its weight. I’m always adding to my long list of places that I want to see when I visit my family here.

Amsterdam is said to have two sides. There’s the charming side: quaint cobblestone streets that lead to picture-perfect canals lined with adorable gabled houses. And there’s the rowdy side: the lively Red Light District where you’ll find strip clubs and “coffee shops” selling cannabis. But there’s so much more to the city—like its many colorful outdoor markets, the street art in the once-abandoned shipyards of Amsterdam-Noord, and the bright tulip fields just beyond the capital. And with seven days, you’ll have the time to explore it all.
